#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:1
msgid ""
"Disable rendering of interior faces that are between cells of different order"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:3
msgid "Motivation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:5
msgid ""
"Local refinement can produce meshes composed by different cell types and "
"multiple degrees.So far, when two volumetric cells of different order are "
"connected by their corners (for instance, a quadratic hexahedron next to a "
"linear hexahedron ), the internal face is rendered and is not considered as "
"a ghost cell. One may want to hide the rendering of these internal faces for "
"multiple reasons:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:7
msgid ""
"When playing with transparency, we don't want to see some faces that can be "
"located in the middle of the geometry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:8
msgid ""
"For big meshes, the rendering of the interior faces can drastically impact "
"the performances. So for this reason, we would like to optionally disable "
"the rendering of internal faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:11
msgid "Implementation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release_details/9.4/add-MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder.md:13
msgid ""
"In this work, the option MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder is added to "
"vtkUnstructuredGridGeometryFilter. The way it's work is that in InsertFace, "
"if MatchBoundariesIgnoringCellOrder is activated, only the cell corners are "
"used to check if two cells are superposed."
msgstr ""
